          <updateDate>2017-07-27T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Relief for Recovering Communities Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Transportation to treat an area as an &quot;urbanized area&quot; following a major disaster under the Disaster Relief Act of 1974 until the second decennial census conducted after such disaster if: (1) the area was defined and designated as such by the Department of Commerce in the decennial census immediately preceding such disaster, effective with the 2000 decennial census; and (2) the population of the area fell below 50,000 as a result of such disaster. This designation as an urbanized area permits an application for federal transit funding based upon population levels in the area prior to the major disaster. </p> <p>An area treated as an urbanized area shall be assigned the population and square miles of the urban cluster designated by Commerce in the most recent decennial census.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
